---
import '../../styles/seventures.css';
---

<div class="relative min-h-screen w-full overflow-hidden bg-neutral-50 text-neutral-800 font-mono">
  <div id="tsparticles"></div>

  <div
    id="cursor"
    class="fixed w-8 h-8 rounded-full border border-neutral-600 pointer-events-none z-50 opacity-60 mix-blend-difference"
  >
  </div>

  <header class="fixed top-0 left-0 w-full p-8 z-40 flex justify-between items-center backdrop-blur-sm bg-neutral-50/30">
    <div class="text-neutral-700 text-xs tracking-widest uppercase">
      <a href="/seventures" class="hover:text-neutral-900 transition-colors">
        <span class="text-neutral-500">$</span> samuel_ernest_ventures<span class="text-neutral-600 animate-cursor-blink">_</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <nav class="hidden md:flex space-x-8">
      <a href="/seventures#ventures" class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider transition-colors text-neutral-500 hover:text-neutral-700">
        ventures
      </a>
      <a href="/seventures#positions" class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider transition-colors text-neutral-800">
        positions
      </a>
      <a href="/seventures#about" class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider transition-colors text-neutral-500 hover:text-neutral-700">
        about
      </a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="container mx-auto px-8 pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-8 text-xs text-neutral-500 font-light">
        <span class="text-neutral-600">$</span> cat ./positions/technical-partner.md
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light mb-6 leading-tight tracking-tighter text-neutral-900">
        TECHNICAL PARTNER // CONSUMER PRODUCT
      </h1>

      <div class="flex items-center mb-12">
        <div class="text-xs text-neutral-600 mr-6">REMOTE</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-neutral-600">FULL-TIME</div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-sm text-neutral-600 font-light leading-relaxed border-t border-neutral-300 pt-10">
        <p>
          Being a Technical Partner at Samuel Ernest Ventures is essentially building and operating at the intersection of engineering, product, and leadership.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Your day-to-day will mirror that of a technical founder - coding across the stack while simultaneously making critical decisions on product direction, design, and growth strategies. You'll oscillate between bringing new products from 0 to 1 and scaling existing ones from 1 to a million. The ideal candidate thrives in ambiguity, moves with velocity, and is passionate about building to create impact at scale.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-10 mb-10">
          <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-700 mb-4">You will</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-xs text-neutral-600">
            <li>Design and engineer full-stack features across our product ecosystem</li>
            <li>Lead and work with other engineers to accelerate development velocity</li>
            <li>Drive ideation, research, prioritization, and prototyping of new product concepts</li>
            <li>Collaborate closely with designers to build intuitive and engaging user interfaces</li>
            <li>Develop and integrate advanced AI/LLM capabilities into consumer products</li>
            <li>Architect systems that scale to millions while maintaining performance</li>
            <li>Run experiments to increase user engagement and drive growth metrics</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 mb-10">
          <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-700 mb-4">We want</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-xs text-neutral-600">
            <li>Strong frontend development experience (React, React Native, Next.js)</li>
            <li>Proficiency in modern backend development (Python, FastAPI)</li>
            <li>Experience with infrastructure as code (AWS CDK, Terraform)</li>
            <li>AI/LLM integration experience is valuable but not required</li>
            <li>Familiarity with design tools like Figma</li>
            <li>Exceptional product sense and ability to translate user needs into technical solutions</li>
            <li>Excellent problem-solving skills with a bias toward action</li>
            <li>Strong communication skills and ability to collaborate in small, high-velocity teams</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-10 mb-10">
          <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-700 mb-4">We offer</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-xs text-neutral-600">
            <li>Ownership and autonomy beyond what you'll find elsewhere</li>
            <li>Competitive compensation: Both cash and significant equity</li>
            <li>The opportunity to build products that reach millions</li>
            <li>A team obsessed with solving hard problems</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="pt-10 border-t border-neutral-300 mt-10">
          <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-700 mb-4">How to apply</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-600 mb-6">
            Send an email to <a href="mailto:build@samuelernest.ventures" class="text-neutral-800 hover:underline">samuel@samuelkatsaros.com</a> with:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-xs text-neutral-600">
            <li>Why you're interested in this role</li>
            <li>Examples of your work (demos, repos, products you've built)</li>
            <li>Your resume or relevant experience</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-600 mt-6">
            We value showing over telling. Demonstrate your abilities through concrete examples.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 text-xs text-neutral-500 font-light flex items-center">
          <a href="/seventures#positions" class="inline-flex items-center group">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-3 w-3 text-neutral-500 group-hover:text-neutral-700 transition-colors mr-2 transform rotate-180">
              <path d="M5 12h14"></path><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span class="group-hover:text-neutral-700 transition-colors">back to positions</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="fixed bottom-0 left-0 w-full p-8 z-40 flex justify-between items-center backdrop-blur-sm bg-neutral-50/30">
    <div class="text-xs text-neutral-500 font-light">
      <span class="text-neutral-600">root@samuel-ernest:~#</span>
    </div>
    <div class="text-xs text-neutral-500 font-light">Â© <span id="year"></span> Samuel Ernest Ventures</div>
  </footer>
</div>

<script>
  // Get the current year for the footer
  document.getElementById('year').textContent = new Date().getFullYear().toString();

  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    // Cursor movement
    const cursor = document.getElementById('cursor');
    
    document.addEventListener('mousemove', function(e) {
      cursor.style.left = `${e.clientX - 16}px`;
      cursor.style.top = `${e.clientY - 16}px`;
      cursor.style.transition = 'transform 0.1s ease-out, opacity 0.3s ease';
      cursor.style.transform = 'translate3d(0, 0, 0)';
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  @keyframes cursor-blink {
    0%, 49% {
      opacity: 1;
    }
    50%, 100% {
      opacity: 0;
    }
  }

  .animate-cursor-blink {
    animation: cursor-blink 1s step-end infinite;
  }
</style> 